result.execSummary:
The defendant Victoria L. Landry was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case. One or more other charges in this case were dismissed. The dismissed charges were not proven and have no legal effect. Victoria L. Landry is presumed innocent of the dismissed charges.

  • Victoria L. Landry was found guilty of Substantial Battery-Intend Bodily Harm [Modifiers: Use of a Dangerous Weapon, Domestic Abuse - Infliction of Physical Pain or Injury], a class I felony, Wisconsin Statutes 940.19(2).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

supervisions.notes: Credit for 88 days served if revoked.  Defendant may petition the court for expungement upon successful completion of the sentence.

miscConds.notes: If probation or extended supervision is revoked or discharged with outstanding financial obligations, a civil judgment shall be entered against the defendant and in favor of restitution victims and governmental entities for the balance due.  Collections may include income assignment.  This applies to all counts and financial obligations.
May not possess any weapons, including firearms.

Obey all of the rules and regulations of supervising probation agent.
*  Pay supervision fees.
Do not possess or consume alcoholic beverages and do not have alcoholic beverages within the residence.  Do not possess or consume controlled substances, except by prescription.  Participate in counseling deemed appropriate by your agent, which may include: alcohol/drug, anger management/DV counseling, psychiatric/psychological, AODA Assessment and follow-through with recommended treatment.
*  Pay all court costs including all applicable surcharges.
*  If unpaid financial obligations remain at discharge or revocation, civil judgment to be entered.
*  Defendant is ordered to submit to a DNA sample & pay the surcharge, notice given to def. in court.
May not possess any weapons, including firearms.  Probation & Parole to notify the court, in writing, upon dirty UA or proof of possession/consumption of alcohol or illegal drugs.

records.addlTxt: Deft released from custody as to this file only.
Conditions of Probation Imposed by the Judge.

Attorney Emily Gaertner appeared for the State. Defendant in custody by zoom w/ Attorney I Mickelson. Clerk/H. Barnett. State in victim rights compliance. On State's motion, ct 2 is dismissed. Deft pleads guilty. Court finds deft guilty. PSI waived. Court withholds sentence and places deft on probation for 2 years w/conditions; credit for 88 days served if revoked; deft to submit DNA sample and pay $250 DNA surcharge; pay $100 DV surcharge. Court finds deft eligible for expunction upon successful completion of probation.
